[normal]:
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Ways of increasing self sufficiency in products for which the UK has a comparative advantage[bold]As demonstrated by Defra stat’s over the years t
[normal]he UK
[normal]’s self-sufficiency has consistently declined 
[normal]from 
[normal]almost 80% in 1984 to around 60% in 2010. W
[normal]e currently import around £37.6bn of food and drink
[normal] which demonstrates that the UK is becoming increasingly dependent on food imports and, at the same time, is one of the few developed countries with a population 
[normal]that is expected to expand significantly over the next few decades.
