[normal]There is 
[normal]consumer appetite for more home-grown food
[normal] products
[normal]. For example, a One Poll (2013) survey revealed that 78% of shoppers believe supermarkets should stock more British Food, whilst 42% revealed that recent 
[normal]issues around food provenance 
[normal]means that are more 
[normal]likely to purchase traceable food produced on British farms. 
[normal]With appropriate legislation the agricultural industry would have increased access to 
[normal]technologies to produce more 
[normal]food in the UK and meet the challenge of sustainable intensification. 
